description.narrative: (USAID West Africa Regional): The West African Health Organization (WAHO) is a regional institution with the mandate to coordinate and harmonize health policies across the 15 member states of the Economic Community of West African States (ECOWAS). In line with USAID Forward reform, USAID/West Africa will support WAHO to strengthen its capacity to lead health efforts in the region. FY 2014 funds will support: strategic planning to align WAHO with the ECOWAS planning process; operationalizing WAHO's health information policy in the 15 member states; operationalizing WAHO's advocacy and communications strategies; continuing a regional forum for best practices in health in West Africa; developing a strategy to engage the private sector on mobile health; strengthening partnerships with other African institutions such as the East, Central and Southern African Community Health Community and the African Union; and exploring a regional platform for maternal and neonatal death review, surveillance and response.
